         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... comparable to bits ... sorrow ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... inclination. Thereupon they compassionately (?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... pity. Away ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... from the deeds ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in the births by cause of the beings ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in this matter. || ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... to become amazed ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... from the <hi>saṃsāra</hi> of the self ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... if he goes into the fire (with his ...?) form, so ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... worth is the fruit. || ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... that he can make silent. His ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>287</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (the king?) has done. To whom you leave him then ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
